Description= 'Precipitate calcite using a TST rate law'
This is part of the EQ3/6 Test Case Library
Precipitate calcite from supersaturated solution at 25C; using a TST-form
rate law (Delany; Puigdomenech; and Wolery; 1986). This is a form of problem
2 from Delany; Puigdomenech; and Wolery (1986; p. 21-22; 34-37); which
simulates an experiment (Run #7) reported by Reddy; Plummer; and Busenberg
This problem was formerly known as pptcala.6i. The original pptcal.6i
test case ran the same problem; but with Plummer's activity term rate law
(see Reddy et al.; 1981). EQ3/6 no longer supports the use of that rate law.
